'''西里尔与美多德'''（{{lang-el|Κύριλλος καὶ Μεθόδιος}}，{{lang-cu|К[[ѷ|ѷ]]риллъ и Ме[[ѳ|ѳ]]одїи}}）是[[东罗马帝国|东罗马帝国]]的著名传教士。在传播基督教正教的同时，他们同为[[西里尔字母|西里尔字母]]的发明做出了巨大贡献。他们同时被[[天主教会|天主教会]]和[[东正教会|东正教会]]封为圣人，被称为“'''圣西里尔和圣美多德'''”。
==简介==
{{main|基里尔 (东罗马帝国传教士)|美多德}}
[[西里尔_(东罗马帝国传教士)|西里尔]]在西元826年或827年出生，原名为“'''康斯坦丁'''”，西里尔是他在[[罗马|罗马]]成为修道士时取的圣名。[[美多德|美多德]]在825年或826年出生<ref name="#1">{{Cite web|title=Methodius of Moravia - OrthodoxWiki|url=https://orthodoxwiki.org/Methodius_of_Moravia|accessdate=2021-04-23|work=orthodoxwiki.org|archive-date=2021-04-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423052526/https://orthodoxwiki.org/Methodius_of_Moravia|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="#1"/><ref>{{Cite web|title=Cyril and Methodius - OrthodoxWiki|url=https://orthodoxwiki.org/Cyril_and_Methodius|accessdate=2021-04-23|work=orthodoxwiki.org|archive-date=2021-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210511060220/https://orthodoxwiki.org/Cyril_and_Methodius|dead-url=no}}</ref>，原名为“'''米哈伊尔'''”，美多德是他在密细亚的[[烏魯達山|奥林匹斯山]]成为修道士时取的圣名<ref>''Cyril and Methodius'', [[大英百科全书|Encyclopedia Britannica]] 2005</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RIdFAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA246|publisher=Böhlau|date=1870|language=de|first=Akademie der Wissenschaften (Wien) Philosophisch-Historische|last=Klasse|title=Denkschriften|pages=246|access-date=2021-04-23|archive-date=2021-04-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423012302/https://books.google.com/books?id=RIdFAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA246|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>Chapter 18 of the Slavonic [http://www.clas.ufl.edu/users/fcurta/Cyril.html ''Life of Constantine''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.clas.ufl.edu/users/fcurta/Cyril.html |date=20121215043926 }}, an English translation</ref><ref>English Translation of the 18th Chapter of the ''Vita Constantini'', [[Liturgy_of_the_Hours|Liturgy of the Hours]], Proper of Saints, 14 February</ref>。他们都出生在[[萨洛尼卡|萨洛尼卡]]（位于现在的[[希腊|希腊]]）<ref>''Columbia Encyclopedia'', Sixth Edition. 2001-05, s.v. "Cyril and Methodius, Saints"; ''Encyclopedia Britannica'', Encyclopedia Britannica Incorporated, Warren E. Preece - 1972, p.846, s.v., "Cyril and Methodius, Saints" and "Eastern Orthodoxy, Missions ancient and modern"; ''Encyclopedia of World Cultures'', David H. Levinson, 1991, 